message:
Hi Stephen, I'm inside a problem and I would like to know if you can help me. I'm new in async messages so I really don't understand how to implement it. My application is running in ASP.NET Framework 4.5.

I receive notificacions from a service. That notification calls to my "MyMethod" passing a json.

This is my current method:
public HttpStatusCodeResult MyMethod()
        {
            try
            {
                StreamReader stream = new StreamReader(Request.InputStream);
                json = stream.ReadToEnd();
                Object myObject = new JavaScriptSerializer().Deserialize<Object>(json);

                bool result = HERE I DO SOMETHING THAT RETURNS TRUE OR FALSE
                if (result)
                     return new HttpStatusCodeResult((int)HttpStatusCode.OK);

                    return new HttpStatusCodeResult((int)HttpStatusCode.InternalServerError);
                }
            }
            catch (Exception ex)
            {
                return new HttpStatusCodeResult((int)HttpStatusCode.InternalServerError);
            }
        }

What's the problem? That services requires the HTTP CODE response in less than 500ms. Now, the "HERE I DO SOMETHING THAT RETURNS TRUE OR FALSE" takes more than 500ms (it takes between 700 and 2000ms generally).

What I need? Return the HTTP CODE before and then process my logic.

Could you give me some code example to know how to implement async messaging (if it's the best solution)?

I would appreciate your help.

Thanks!

Ariel
